*description_start
This smaller spider is pale skinned with liver colored spots spread out over its roughly two foot body. It scampers back and forth along the everpresent webbing with ease.
*description_end
texe A small shape jumps in, leaping from web to web.
texg A small shape drops down from above.
texd falls over to lay on its back, legs curled.
texm A smaller spider scoots up and to the
texa A spider drops towards
texs A spider's back legs blur as it draws webbing from its abdomen.
texl A spider flings a mass of webbing at
texq A mass of webbing misses its target.
tex1 A chittering sound echoes in the darkness, as if from a hundred sources.
tex2 Several dark shapes flit by at eye level in the webbing.
