NUMBER 66
NAME Temple of Shin-jah, Inner Temple 
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CHANNEL 147
REGION 5
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a square meditation chamber. The flickering yellow glare of four
butter lamps quarter the room, picking out the tarnished sheen of metallic
embroidery amoungst the ancient-looking tapestries that overhang the walls.
The floor is black marble, its center covered by a darkly patterned carpet
of silk brocade. A number of flat brocaded black cushions are scattered around
the carpet to provide seating. Each of the four corners of the room is
dominated by the presence of a heavy, triple-edged dagger standing as tall and
bulky as a man, set upright by its point in a stand fashioned in the shape of
an equilateral triangle. Thus positioned, the daggers have the look almost of
sentries on guard. The pommel ends of the huge daggers bear intricate traceries
of carving, in patterns reminiscent of grinning masks. The wavering light from
the butter lamps give the carvings the disquieting illusion of movement, as if
the weapons themselves harbor some malevolent life of their own. More glints of
gold and silver are seen from the chambers vaulted ceiling. Along the north
wall is a small altar.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 65
;----------------------------altar------------------------
ITEM 0 236 ADJ1=25 ADJ2=218
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The smaller sacrificial altar to Shin-jah is ornately carved with the grinning faces of demonic beings. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------------------ceiling--------------------------
ITEM 1 482 
